vement and abolition during the nineteenth and twentieth centuries. In this way, Baghoolizadeh makes visible the people and histories that were erased from Iran and its diaspora.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / Middle Eastern Studies.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478059257?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478059257423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478059257/original  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles